      {
        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "## Interpretation\n\nThe clearest signal is that **Hg²⁺ binds sulfur donors much more strongly than the representative N- or O-donor ligands**. Nitrogen donors can still bind well, especially chelating ones like **ethylenediamine**, but they do not generally match the top sulfur-donor values. Oxygen-donor systems are weaker and more variable, and in the Hg²⁺ case often compete with hydrolysis/speciation effects.\n\nThat trend is also chemically sensible: **Hg²⁺ is a soft Lewis acid**, so it should favor **soft sulfur bases** over harder oxygen donors.",
